        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 15 at 2:02AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 201 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 17
miles northwest of Codman, or 19 miles north of Pampa, moving
southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southwestern
Roberts County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
